.

The suture line of specimen MB.C.3633 has a wide external lobe; this is subdivided by a median saddle that has a height of two thirds of the external lobe depth (
Fig. 14A
). The prongs of the external lobe are slightly asymmetric and V-shaped. On the flank follows a V-shaped lateral lobe and, on the umbilial margin, a broadly rounded umbilical lobe.
